Greek, Troika Meeting Held in ‘Positive’ Climate, Official Says

-- B y   M a r i a   P e t r a k i s
-- 
2011-09-29T15:02:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/greek-troika-meeting-held-in-positive-climate-official-says.html
Greek Finance Minister Evangelos
Venizelos’s first meeting with the heads of a European Union,
 International Monetary Fund  and European Central Bank mission
was held in a positive and creative climate, according to a
Greek finance ministry official.  The officials, known as the troika, and Venizelos reviewed
recent austerity measures announced by the Greek government,
said the official, who declined to be named. They will hold more
meetings with Venizelos and other government members over the
next few days, according to the official.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maria Petrakis at 
 mpetrakis@bloomberg.net  